column1: Which ensemble will win the 2020 Screen Actors Guild Award for Outstanding Performance by an Ensemble in a Comedy Series?
column5: ['A tie or other outcome', 'Barry', 'Fleabag', 'The Kominsky Method', 'The Marvelous Mrs. Maisel', "Schitt's Creek"]

column6: There are a lot of different forces at play, such as politics, critical acclaim, and viewership. Plus Hollywood people like to give us surprises, so I've put a little probability on that. This is how I think the probabilities settle out.

Barry is laugh-out-loud (dark) funny ('ninja girl'!) but apparently not watched as much (?) as other shows. Mrs. Maisel is a good series, is popular and reflects (and a retro way) the current #MeToo and pro-LGBT era ethos. Fleabag has good buzz from friends of mine. All good, character-driven shows.
Because i really like fleabag but I don't think it will win
With the emphasis on women-led projects and based on press coverage, it seems these two programs have the inside track.
